-- UK motor insurer Admiral's turnover dips in first quarter 
-- 
-- Wed May 14, 2014 02:21AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, May 14 (Reuters) - British auto insurer Admiral Group Plc <ADML.L> posted a 7 percent drop in turnover in the first three months of 2014 despite a 6 percent increase in customers, amid sliding UK car insurance premiums.

In a trading statement on Wednesday, the Cardiff-based insurance group announced turnover of 514 million pounds ($865.49 million), down from 551 million pounds for the same period last year. Total premiums were down 11 percent year-on-year.